Program: Discovery
Title: Saving the brain - part four
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry69
Last Broadcast Date: 20 August 2002
Can the brain help heal itself after an injury or illness? A look at attempts to rehabilitate those who have suffered a stroke or brain injury. Until recently physiotherapy was the main form of treatment, but new methods of helping reverse the damage are now being used.